## Why This Is Asked

This question probes real-world streaming semantics, multi-tenant isolation, and data contracts in GCP with practical rollback.

## Key Concepts

- Dataflow exactly-once processing
- Tenant-level dedupe by (tenant_id, txn_id)
- Watermarks for late events
- Parquet in Cloud Storage + incremental BigQuery loading
- Data Catalog contracts and lineage
- 24h rollback and backfill test plan

## Code Example

```javascript
// Pseudo Dataflow-like dedupe (illustrative)
class DedupFn {
  process(element) {
    const key = element.tenant_id + '|' + element.txn_id;
    if (!state.has(key)) {
      state.add(key);
      return element;
    }
    return null;
  }
}
```

## Follow-up Questions

- How would you verify exactly-once behavior under backpressure and late data?
- How would you roll back a fraudulent day’s data within 24h?
